  "text": "1.5 \"-\" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" \" Additionally, Neuhoff and Gilbert [CITATION_1] show that for a memoryless source, R;!G equals the lower convex enve lope of all memoryless encoders for this source. Thus,",
